The paper focuses on designing a machine learning-enhanced hybrid fuzzing system, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and security (cs.CR) aspects. The system uses code reachability and dynamic analysis to extract features, which are then used to train a supervised machine learning model (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the implementation of the system using Python and LLVM (cs.PL), and its applicability to various kinds of programs (cs.SY).
